    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-11-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-11-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="1819"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1819">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 367.11/16.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Ambassador to Great Britain</gloss>.</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d1819fn1">The same to the American Ambassador to Russia.
                        (File No. 367.11/18.)</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-11-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 11, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Convey to Minister for Foreign Affairs the gratification of this Government upon
                    learning that its desires had been anticipated by the British Government in
                    relation to protection of Americans at Constantinople.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
